section.section:
"Reportable offense" means:
A crime of violence, as defined in § 14-101 of the Criminal Law Article;
Any of the offenses enumerated in § 3-8A-03(d)(4) of the Courts Article;
A violation of § 4-101, § 4-102, § 4-203, or § 4-204 of the Criminal Law Article;
A violation of §§ 5-602 through 5-609, §§ 5-612 through 5-614, § 5-617, § 5-618, § 5-627, or § 5-628 of the Criminal Law Article;
A violation of § 4-503, § 9-504, or § 9-505 of the Criminal Law Article;
A violation of § 6-102, § 6-103, § 6-104, or § 6-105 of the Criminal Law Article;
A violation of § 9-802 or § 9-803 of the Criminal Law Article;
A violation of § 3-203 of the Criminal Law Article;
A violation of § 6-301 of the Criminal Law Article;
A violation of § 9-302, § 9-303, or § 9-305 of the Criminal Law Article; or
A violation of § 7-105 of the Criminal Law Article.
